NAME
	cpu-gauge (display) - render a headline value and bar sparkline from a current-sample file and a timestamped history file

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay)

READS
	cpu/current	single line: pct busy total (three ints)
	cpu/history	one line per sample: ts pct, oldest first

MOUNT
	Point this module at the outdir of a service that produces
	cpu/current and cpu/history.  A service's outdir is
	/tmp/matrix/<service-name>, so with sysmon-svc the mount is
	/tmp/matrix/sysmon-svc (cpu/current then resolves under it).
	Include that service in the same composition (e.g.
	`service sysmon-svc /`) so its outdir is populated.

WRITES
	none (renders only)

DESCRIPTION
	Draws the current percentage as a headline with busy/total process
	counts, and the history column as a right-aligned 2px-column bar
	sparkline scaled 0-100, with min/max readout.  Re-reads both files
	on every update tick.  No pointer or key handling.

SEE ALSO
	sysmon-svc (produces cpu/current and cpu/history in its outdir)
